ic growth are not capable of acting with prudence to deal with these mega-risks before they become a real danger. He identifies certain institutional design flaws that, while underwriting economic growth, leave society open to potentially catastrophic failure and reveals how these design flaws have been compounded by the stresses of the growing income inequality in society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aClimatxChangementsxGestion du risquexCanada. 0aClimatxChangementsxGestion du risquexÉtats-Unis. 0aClimatic changesxRisk managementxCanada. 0aClimatic changesxRisk managementxUnited States. 0aClimatic changesxRisk managementzCanada. 0aClimatic changesxRisk managementzUnited States. 0aDéveloppement économiquexCanada. 0aDéveloppement économiquexÉtats-Unis. 0aEconomic developmentxCanada. 0aEconomic developmentxUnited States. 0aEconomic developmentzCanada. 0aEconomic developmentzUnited States. 0aIndustrial policyxCanada. 0aIndustrial policyxUnited States. 0aIndustrial policyzCanada. 0aIndustrial policyzUnited States. 0aPolitique industriellexCanadaxCanadaxUnited States. 0aPolitique industriellexÉtats-Unis. 0aPower resourcesxEnvironmental aspectsxCanada. 0aPower resourcesxEnvironmental aspectsxUnited States. 0aPower resourcesxEnvironmental aspectszCanada. 0aPower resourcesxEnvironmental aspectszUnited States. 0aRessources énergétiquesxAspect de l'environnementxCanada. 0aRessources énergétiquesxAspect de l'environnementxÉtats-Unis. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Economic Policy.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2013z978311127412608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2013z978311127715840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978155339507240uhttps://ww